definition.value: A glycotetraosylceramide having beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose as the tetrasaccharide component.
An ethanediol that is ethane-1,2-diol in which a hydrogen attached to a carbon is replaced by a 3,4-dimethoxyphenyl group.
A N-acyl-L-amino acid  that is L-glutamine in which one of the hydrogens attached to the alpha-amino group is replaced by an acyl group.
A GDP-fucose in which the fucosyl residue has L-configuration.
